 ejecta forms\ncompact ($\\lesssim10^{15}$ cm) optically-thick CSM at the time of core\ncollapse; though only directly observable via rapid post-explosion spectroscopy\n($\\lesssim$ few days before being overtaken by the SN ejecta), this material\ncan boost the SN luminosity via shock interaction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2022 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Aug 2022 18:15:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
