. Waheed, E. Wang, M.-Z. Wang, M. Watanabe, E. Won, X. Xu, B. D.\n  Yabsley, W. Yan, S. B. Yang, J. H. Yin, C. Z. Yuan, Y. Yusa, Y. Zhai, Z. P.\n  Zhang, V. Zhilich, V. Zhukova","title":"Measurement of the branching fraction of $\\Xi_{c}^{0}\\to\n  \\Lambda_{c}^{+}\\pi^{-}$ at Belle","comments":"5 pages, 4 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":"Belle Preprint 2022-06; KEK Preprint 2022-4","categories":"hep-ex","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Based on a data sample of 983 fb$^{-1}$ collected with the Belle detector at\nthe KEKB asymmetric-energy $e^+e^-$ collider, we present the study of the\nheavy-flavor-conserving decay $\\Xi_{c}^{0}\\to \\Lambda_{c}^{+}\\pi^{-}$ with\n$\\Lambda_{c}^{+}$ reconstructed via its $pK^{-} \\pi^{+}$ decay mode. The\nbranching fraction ratio $\\mathcal{B}(\\Xi_{c}^{0}\\to\n\\Lambda_{c}^{+}\\pi^{-})/\\mathcal{B}(\\Xi_{c}^{0}\\to \\Xi^{-}\\pi^{+})$ is measured\nto be $0.38 \\pm 0.04 \\pm 0.04$. Combing with the world average value of\n$\\mathcal{B}(\\Xi_{c}^{0}\\to \\Xi^{-}\\pi^{+})$, the branching fraction\n$\\mathcal{B}(\\Xi_{c}^{0}\\to \\Lambda_{c}^{+}\\pi^{-})$ is deduced to be $(0.54\n\\pm 0.05 \\pm 0.05 \\pm 0.12)\\%$. Here, the uncertainties above are statistical,\nsystematic, and from $\\mathcal{B}(\\Xi_c^{0} \\to \\Xi^{-}\\pi^{+})$, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Jun 2022 03:23:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2022 04:39:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2022 10:29:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-30"}
