{"id":"2206.08711","submitter":"Pavel Muraev","authors":"P. S. Muraev, D. N. Maksimov, A. R. Kolovsky","title":"Ballistic transport of interacting Bose particles in the tight-binding\n  chain","comments":"6 figures, 7 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1103/PhysRevE.106.064203","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.other","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  It is known that quantum transport of non-interacting Bose particles across\nthe tight-binding chain is ballistic in the sense that the current does not\ndepend on the chain length. We address the question whether the transport of\nstrongly interacting bosons can be ballistic as well. We find such a regime and\nshow that, classically, it corresponds to the synchronized motion of local\nnon-linear oscillators. It is also argued that, unlike the case of\nnon-interacting bosons, the transporting state responsible for the ballistic\ntransport of interacting bosons is metastable, i.e., the current decays in\ncourse of time. An estimate for the decay time is obtained.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Jun 2022 12:05:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-21"}
